title: be my only
body:
…in which Y/N and Harry return to Holmes Chapel after a storm destroyed their treehouse. 

  • Second book of the My Girl Trilogy.
  • AU: actor!harry, older!harry, younger!y/n; (4-year age gap)
  • Preview: Every Thursday // Chapter: Every Friday (Wattpad) and Saturday (Tumblr) // 12pm GMT.

To encourage more reads on Wattpad, I’ll update the Wattpad book (with the original character named Thea, not Y/N) 1 day earlier than on Tumblr. So instead of waiting 2 days after a preview for a new chapter, you can read it the next day on Wattpad.

Chapter 1: FIRE AND RAIN [Preview - May 23 // Chapter - May 24 (WATTPAD) and May 25 (TUMBLR) // 12pm GMT] - Harry and Y/N go back to where it ended.

✰ Drabbles

  16. The Only Exception - Paramore

summary: I highly highly doubt that Columbia would reduce Harry's initial deal to a much lesser one. All the tabloids reported the $80M...
question: I highly highly doubt that Columbia would reduce Harry's initial deal to a much lesser one. All the tabloids reported the $80M deal after he was officially signed under Columbia. Why would they do that and make up lies if the deal wasn't that high? It makes no sense. With Harry's relevancy and status in the industry and in Hollywood in general, I doubt Columbia would play mind tricks with him. They knew from the start who was the breakthrough member from 1D. Everybody knew. Part 1
answer:
Part 2- Apple’s $25M offer for one album raised Harry’s bidding value even more which led to Columbia to throw in the money. Apple agreed to pay $75M for 3 albums. So Columbia’s $80M deal makes sense. That’s the only way for them to snatch Harry under their roster. I doubt they would reduce it to 60M when there is another deal by another company which is higher than that. If that’s the case, Apple would have had the rights for Harry, not Columbia. Jeff did a good job in sealing the deal well.

Jeff did a fantastic job. According to Harry hater Andrew, all those figures you mention are fanciful. He just can’t cope with his fave Niall being offered $75m less.
